<law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection amended="yes" chaptername="Crimes And Punishments" id="id00" statutenumber="28-371"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>28-371</statuteno><catchline id="id00">Vulnerable adult, defined.</catchline><para>Vulnerable adult means any person eighteen years of age or older who has a substantial mental or functional impairment or for whom a guardian or conservator has been appointed under the Nebraska Probate Code.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1988, LB 463, &#167; 24; </para><para>Laws 2016, LB934, &#167; 7. </para><effectivedate>April 19, 2016</effectivedate></source><crossreference><para><emphasis>Nebraska Probate Code,</emphasis> see section 30-2201.</para></crossreference></law>
